name: Where’s my voice
description: When was the last time you tried to scream? Pent up emotions all rush out at once at the top of your lungs. All the anger, frustration, out. Can you still scream? Do you still have the energy? Are you even allowed to? Or do the rules state to calmly accept all the bullshit that keeps getting tossed on you? Has it piled up so much that you can’t take it anymore? Wessel ‘21
